st-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T_{2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.13889em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> attempt to grab each other's resources <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">x</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>However, they can't acquire them because they are locked</li>\n<li>Meaning, they will continue waiting forever for each other's resource</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Illustrating Deadlocks from Old Crime Scenes</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Imagine a criminal and a cop are at a standoff with each other</li>\n<li>The criminal holds a hostage, while the cop holds the criminal's friend</li>\n<li>The criminal and cop will only release their held person if the other releases their person first</li>\n<li>Specifically, the cop will only release the criminal's friend if the criminal releases the hostage first</li>\n<li>Similarly, the criminal will only release the hostage if the cop releases the criminal's friend first</li>\n<li>Therefore, they are at a deadlock:</li>\n<li>\n<p>In this analogy, the characters represent:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Cop:</code> Thread 1</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Criminal:</code> Thread 2</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Hostage:</code> Resource 1</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Criminal&#39;s Friend:</code> Resource 2</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In this analogy, the following can be translated:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Thread 1 demands resource 2, but thread 2 owns the lock</li>\n<li>Thread 2 demands resource 1, but thread 1 owns the lock</li>\n<li>The owner of resource 2 is thread 1</li>\n<li>The owner of resource 1 is thread 2</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>References</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://index-of.co.uk/Python/Python%20Essential%20Reference,%20Fourth%20Edition.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Python Essential References</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/threading.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Documentation for Threading API</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/34550/12777044\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Race Conditions with Locking</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/34520/12777044\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Example of a Deadlock</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/35640575/12777044\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Crime Example of Deadlocks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/3130212/12777044\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Illustrating Race Conditions with Transactions</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"py/threading/deadlock","previousSlug":"py/threading/timer","nextSlug":"py/threading/lock","previousTitle":"threading.Timer","nextTitle":"threading.Lock"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}